        As a freelance game developer, you will be responsible for the following tasks:
        
        Collaborate with the game design team to understand the concept, gameplay mechanics, and overall vision for the project.
        
        Develop and implement game features, mechanics, and systems using Unity and C#.
        
        Ensure the game runs smoothly across different platforms, optimizing performance and addressing any technical challenges.
        
        Participate in regular meetings to discuss progress, provide updates, and address feedback.
        
        Work closely with artists and designers to integrate visual elements and enhance the overall gaming experience.
        
        Troubleshoot and debug any issues that arise during the development process.
        
        Keep up-to-date with industry trends and incorporate innovative ideas into the game development process.

